attributes.gcd: Refers to the unique identifier of the account or contract held by the customer. Account number is defined as numbers, letters or alphanumeric code assigned to every significant customer, supplier and lender for ease of reference in accounting records of the financial institution.
Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.
Refers to the country from which it is anticipated that this account is to receive a wire transfer.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.

Flag to indicate if the account balance is in debit or in credit. If the value is updated as D means the balance is in debit and if the value is updated as C means the balance is in credit. Debit balance will indicate the amount which is due and credit balance is the amount which could arise due to overpayment of the cycle balance.
Refers to the average amount expressed in base currency of a transaction of the profile metric that is anticipated for this account during this profile period.
Refers to the average total monetary amount expressed in base currency of all transactions of the profile metric that is anticipated for this account during this profile period.
Refers to the average number of transactions of the profile metric that is anticipated for this account during this profile period.
Refers to the higher end of the range of expected total transaction amounts of the profile metric for this account expressed in base currency during this profile period.
Refers to the higher end of the range of expected transaction amounts of the profile metric for this account expressed in base currency during this profile period.
Refers to the lower end of the range of expected total transaction amounts of the profile metric for this account expressed in base currency during this profile period.
Refers to the lower end of the range of expected transaction amounts of the profile metric for this account expressed in base currency during this profile period.
Refers to the Metric measured by this anticipatory profile record (for example, USD-CASH-USD Cash, DOM-WIRE-Domestic Wire, FRN-CHK-Foreign Check etc.).
Refers to the Unit of Period of time that this anticipatory profile represents. List of values are: D Daily,W Weekly,M Monthly,Q Quarterly,S Semi-Annually,A Annually.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.
